verse_part: that were able to put on
And when thou art come in,
And when he had taken him,
And when she was come in
and him that is shut up
and he trode her under foot.
And when he was come in,
as soon as he had made an end
that it be not broken down.
and they put up in bags,
according unto that which is written
the women therein that were with child
and carried [the people of] it captive
And when they were come up,
and I will cause him to fall
have I brought it to pass,
and I will turn thee back
such things as grow of themselves,
that which springeth of the same;
and that I shall go up
they might provoke me to anger
and in the places round about
